[2] Montana (Ravalli County)
Date: Tue 17 Apr 2012
Source: NBC Montana [edited]
http://www.nbcmontana.com/news/30910437/detail.html


Ravalli County reported one more pertussis case Tuesday [17 Apr 2012]. That's a total of 15 confirmed whooping cough cases in the Bitterroot.

The latest case is another child. 14 children are now sick with pertussis. Only one adult has tested positive. Most of the cases are in Pinesdale. Some are in the Corvallis area.

"The Corvallis school system is increasing surveillance," said public health director Judy Griffin. "The school nurse has been diligently talking with teachers and possible contacts."

[Byline: Kevin Maki]

