******
[3] North Carolina (multiple counties)
Date: Tue 17 Apr 2012
Source: MyFox 8 [edited]
http://myfox8.com/2012/04/17/whooping-cough-outbreak-spreads-to-randolph-county/


Randolph County has 15 cases of pertussis, also known as whooping cough, and health director Mimi Cooper said many of the cases are related to the 129 cases in Alamance County. "We can connect those children to each other. They've spent time with each other during the period the children were incubating the disease," Cooper said.

Guilford County has had 5 cases of whooping cough in 2012. Cooper said those cases were also related to the Alamance outbreak, but the Guilford County Health Department could not confirm that.

Cooper said pertussis, which can be fatal in infants younger than 6 months, is that serious of an infliction. "It's not intended to be punishing for the children or the school. We are trying to prevent children from dying," Cooper said.

[Byline: Mitch Carr]

